  "text": "Traced the Envoy connection pool overflow error 'upstream connect error or disconnect/reset before headers. reset reason: overflow' to its source. The error chain: (1) Circuit breaker thresholds (max_connections, max_pending_requests, max_requests) are defined in envoy/config/cluster/v3/circuit_breaker.proto in data-plane-api. (2) ResourceManagerImpl (resource_manager_impl.h) enforces these thresholds via ManagedResourceImpl.canCreate(). (3) ConnPoolImplBase.newStreamImpl() in conn_pool_base.cc checks pendingRequests().canCreate() and triggers PoolFailureReason::Overflow when exceeded. (4) UpstreamRequest.onPoolFailure() in upstream_request.cc maps PoolFailureReason::Overflow to StreamResetReason::Overflow. (5) Filter.onUpstreamReset() in router.cc generates the error message using Utility::resetReasonToString(). (6) resetReasonToString() in utility.cc maps Overflow to 'overflow'. The StreamResetReason::Overflow enum is defined in stream_reset_handler.h. Overflow resets are never retried (retry_state_impl.cc returns NoRetry for Overflow).",
